<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Schizoid_personality_disorder&amp;action=edit&amp;section=27" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.thebreeces.com/schizoid_a_personality_not_a_disorder.html" class="external text" title="http://www.thebreeces.com/schizoid_a_personality_not_a_disorder.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Oppressed Group: Schizoid, A Personality, Not a Disorder</i></a>: An essay defending the position that SPD is not a valid mental disorder.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2006/11/21/health/psychology/21case.html?ex=1321765200&amp;en=6030af72aae03e77&amp;ei=5088partner=rssnyt&amp;emc=rss" class="external text" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2006/11/21/health/psychology/21case.html?ex=1321765200&amp;en=6030af72aae03e77&amp;ei=5088partner=rssnyt&amp;emc=rss" rel="nofollow">NY Times article "Like a Fish Needs a Bicycle: For Some People, Intimacy Is Toxic"</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.ptypes.com/schizoidpd2.html" class="external text" title="http://www.ptypes.com/schizoidpd2.html" rel="nofollow">A Comprehensive Profile of Schizoid Personality Disorder</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.schizoids.net/forum" class="external text" title="http://www.schizoids.net/forum" rel="nofollow">Schizoid forums</a>: A forum for people with schizoid personality dedicated to research and understanding of this disorder.</li>
</ul>
<table class="navbox" cellspacing="0" style=";">
